<seg id="1045">& Povray; supports two methods of super-sampling. the default is an adaptive, non-recursive method; adaptively because the super-sampling is the adjacent pixels with one. the second method is adaptive-recursive; recursively because each pixel is separated again and again and adaptively because the recursion depth depends on the calculated color values.</seg>
<seg id="1046">If you choose the first method, POV-Ray pursues a ray per pixel. if the difference between the color values to the adjacent pixels crosses the specified threshold, then both pixels are calculated by tracking a certain additional number of pixels with super-sampling. if you set the depth value to 4, a grid of 4x4 additional points will be calculated, with a depth value of 5 then 5x5 (25) additional rays each pixel.</seg>
<seg id="1047">The difference between two pixels is calculated as follows: r 1, g 1 and b 1 the values for red, green and blue of the first pixel, r 2, g 2 and b 2 are the values for red, green and blue of the second pixel. the difference is then:</seg>
